<br />
<br />No offence/rudeness intended, but it would really help the guy if he was linked a proper, 100% accurate pinout mapping from mask ROM to EEPROM or Flash.  This kind of response mimics what I've gotten from the nesdev community over the years when asking how to re-wire an MMC3 cart to permit EEPROMs (the response of which always is "it's not that hard, you just map pin X to pin Y based on the function of the pin", which though true is <strong>far</strong> from what all is required, pin-mapping-wise).

		

